{"result": "{"url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guarani_mythology","title":"Guarani mythology - Wikipedia","description":"The Guarani mythology is the set of narratives about the gods and spirits of the different Tupi-Guarani peoples, ancient and current. Together with the cosmogonies, anthropogonies and rituals, they form part of the religion of these peoples. The Guarani people live in the south-central part ..."}
{"url":"https://www.ancient-origins.net/myths-legends-americas/[REDACTED_TOKEN]","title":"The Gods of Creation and Legendary Beasts of the Guarani | Ancient Origins","description":"Tupa is the supreme god of the Guarani creation myth. According to their mythology, Tupa came from the sun, and with the help of the moon goddess, Arasy, he descended upon a hill in Aregúa, Paraguay, where he stood and created the universe and all of humanity."}
{"url":"https://www.rutaverdebolivia.com/[REDACTED_TOKEN]/","title":"The toborochi tree and the Guaraní legend - Ruta Verde Tours","description":"The Bolivian (Guaraní origin) legend over the toborochi says that long time ago, a beautiful pregnant princess called Araverá (<strong>Sparkle in the sky</strong>) hid inside a tree to give birth to the (colibrí) hummingbird god’s child."}
{"url":"https://simonsparaguay.com/the-guarani-creation-myth/","title":"The Guarani Creation Myth - Simons Paraguay","description":"That tale is for another day, but for now it is enough to say that the children brought forth by their union were cursed and became the seven monsters of Guarani mythology."}
{"url":"https://www.behindthename.com/submit/names/usage/guarani","title":"Guarani Submitted Names - Behind the Name","description":"Aratiri m Guarani Means &quot;ray, bolt, lightning&quot; in Guarani. Aravera m Guarani Means &quot;<strong>flash of lightning</strong>&quot; in Guarani."}
{"url":"https://www.behindthename.com/submit/names/language/tupi","title":"Tupi Submitted Names - Behind the Name","description":"Aravera m Guarani Means &quot;<strong>flash of lightning</strong>&quot; in Guarani. Bartira f Tupi, Brazilian Possibly an archaic variant of Potira. Bartira was the name of the daughter of the chief Tibiriçá, an indigenous leader of great importance for the formation of the city of São Paulo..."}
{"url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Guaran%C3%AD_people","title":"Guaraní people - Wikipedia","description":"While the term Cayua is sometimes still used to refer to settlements of Indigenous peoples who have not well integrated into the dominant society, the modern usage of the name Guarani is generally extended to include all people of native origin regardless of societal status. Barbara Ganson writes that the name Guaraní was given by the Spanish since it means &quot;warrior&quot; in the Tupi-Guaraní dialect spoken there."}
{"url":"https://www.folklore.earth/culture/guarani/","title":"Guarani Mythology | Mythosphere","description":"This article provides an overview of the Guarani belief system, mythology, and rituals, with a focus on deities, heroes, and mythological creatures."}
{"url":"https://mythus.fandom.com/wiki/Brazilian_mythology","title":"Brazilian mythology | Myth and Folklore Wiki | Fandom","description":"The seven are considered primary figures in Guarani mythology, and while several of the lesser gods or even the original humans are forgotten in the verbal tradition of some areas, these seven are generally kept in the legends. Some are considered real even in modern times, in rural areas or indigenous regions."}
{"url":"https://www.reddit.com/r/asklatinamerica/comments/9x36e5/[REDACTED_TOKEN]/","title":"r/asklatinamerica on Reddit: Looking for information about Guarani mythology - what myths, information, depictions do you know of?","description":"Theres this page named Portal Guarani, who tries to save all content made by paraguayans. This page has a subsection about Mythology, which includes guarani mythology, local mythology and mythology from the other etnic groups around, sadly theres no way to separate &quot;just guarani&quot; or &quot;just paraguay only&quot;, and the page looks like it was made in the 90&#x27;s so theres a lot of textwalls."}"}

